tourBios.exmtStatus: Conditionally Exempt: 45th qualifier from Qualifying Tournament, Money List 61-100
tourBios.curYearHigh: Received Northern Trust Open Exemption, which provides an opportunity to a top golfer who represents the advancement of diversity in golf. In his first PGA TOUR start, made the cut, finishing T42 to earn $23,760. Brother Joshua was the 2010 recipient of the Exemption.
tourBios.carHigh: 2012: Advanced to the final stage of the PGA TOUR Qualifying Tournament for the first time and earned conditional status on the Web.com Tour after finishing T130.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Graduated from Riverside Poly High School in 2006 in Riverside, Calif...Golf team was 18-2 and won the Ivy League title...Played high school basketball in 2004-05.
tourBios.personal: Brother Joshua played golf at USC...His relative Randall Hunt is a professional golfer...Favorite golf memory is making a hole-in-one in the Junior World Championship at age 7...Favorite part of golf is putting...Favorite gadgets are RC racecars.
